channel.title: I need a small amount of help regarding port forwarding
channel.description: Okay, I've done everything I need for my server but when I compile it, it works, then when I run it, it says to me "Error: Unable to startup listener on 43594 - Port already in use?" So what do I do to fix this?

item.title: I need a small amount of help regarding port forwarding
item.dc:creator: @maddogshredder maddogshredder
item.description:
@maddogshredder wrote:

Okay, thanks, I’ll try restarting my comp.[br][br][size=1]Posted on: October 11, 2008, 12:58:48 am[/size][hr]Finally fixed it, turns out there was a program on startup called client that was hogging the port, dunno how it got there. Thanks for your help though.

you have more than one program using the port you port forwarded on, don’t have two compilers running at once, or restart your computer
